  "response": "## Finding: `crime_00022` — Sync I/O in Hot Path\n\n**File:** `src/api/files.ts`, lines 12, 13, 15 (inside `loadPlanSchema`)\n\n**Evidence (verbatim):**\n- `` `existsSync` @L12 in `loadPlanSchema` (domain function) ``\n- `` `statSync` @L13 in `loadPlanSchema` (domain function) ``\n- `` `readFileSync` @L15 in `loadPlanSchema` (domain function) ``\n- \"lines: 12, 13, 15\"\n- \"swap for the async variant (`readFile`, `writeFile`, `exec`, …) and `await` it\"\n\n**Blocking calls:** `fs.existsSync`, `fs.statSync`, `fs.readFileSync` — three synchronous filesystem calls per request inside `loadPlanSchema`, each parking the Node event loop until the disk responds. Under concurrent load this serializes every request behind file I/O, which is exactly the p99/event-loop-lag signature.\n\n**Smallest async migration (preserves public signature shape — return type widens to `Promise<…>`):**\n\n```ts\nimport { readFile, stat } from \"node:fs/promises\";\n\nexport async function loadPlanSchema(): Promise<PlanSchema> {\n  try {\n    const info = await stat(SCHEMA_PATH);   // replaces existsSync + statSync\n    if (!info.isFile()) throw new Error(\"schema path is not a file\");\n    const raw = await readFile(SCHEMA_PATH, \"utf8\");\n    return JSON.parse(raw);\n  } catch (err: any) {\n    if (err?.code === \"ENOENT\") throw new Error(\"plan schema missing\");\n    throw err;\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThen `await loadPlanSchema()` at every call site. Notes:\n- `stat` throwing `ENOENT` subsumes the `existsSync` check — one syscall instead of two.\n- Function name, arguments, and resolved value stay identical; only the wrapper goes from `T` to `Promise<T>`.\n- No caching added — the fix is removing the blocking call, per the scenario.",
